CARDINAL POINT LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Cardinal Point LLC ("Cardinal Point") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Cardinal Point generating facility ("Cardinal Point Facility").
Cardinal Point is a wind generating facility located in McDonough and Warren Counties, Illinois. The Cardinal Point Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Cardinal Points' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Cardinal Point Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Cardinal Point's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Cardinal Point shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $1,155,340.36. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $96,278.36.
